## Proposed Changes

To prepare for production deployment, we need to handle the environment variables correctly. 

During local development, `nedai-web` uses a Vite proxy (`/api`) to avoid CORS issues and connect to your local backend. In production, we don't use this proxy.

### 1. Environment Variables Configuration
We will need to set the production environment variables in your deployment platform dashboard (Vercel or Render):

- `VITE_API_BASE_URL`: **`https://nedai-server-yrta.onrender.com/api/v1`** (Instead of the local `/api/v1`)
- `VITE_SERVER_ORIGIN`: **`https://nedai-server-yrta.onrender.com`**

### 2. No Code Changes Needed
No code changes are strictly necessary right now, as your `src/lib/http.ts` and `src/lib/env.ts` are already set up to consume `VITE_API_BASE_URL`. We just need to make sure the environment variables are injected correctly during the build process on the chosen platform.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` locally to verify the production build succeeds without TypeScript or bundling errors.

### Manual Verification
- Deploy the application.
- Visit the public URL provided by the deployment platform.
- Ensure the application loads correctly.
- Test logging in or fetching data to verify that the frontend correctly communicates with the Render backend API without CORS issues.
